caption: amazing  will be back our first  visit  not our last
Great food and service.
The lamb lollipops were amazing! Just wish there was more!😋😋

You're definitely paying for the vibe/experience here. I wasn't impressed with the sliders that I got, but the fries were delicious. The roof seating was closed when we went due to weather so maybe we will go back when the roof seating is open to see what that is like. My wife had gotten a steak and that was very very good. Staff was very attentive and friendly.
Friendly staff. Good food.
Solid casual above average restaurant. Got the special which was a honey glazed pork chop. Didn’t disappoint at all! Really enjoyed the Brussels sprouts.
Very good atmosphere food and drinks all around very relaxing and will return soon
Good service. Good beer. Tacos were great. Nachos were not very good
Roof top is great atmosphere
Great food and service there was a amazing young lady performing.
It's a cute place. Modern and Trendy. The food was good, but nothing to rave about!
We've never had a bad experience at ROM. Always pleasant and worth the money.
Great experience, didn't have reservations but was allowed in, service was excellent, food was great as well
Went there for brunch, and even on valentine's day the staff was quick and courteous and food was tasty. Live music was good and played at an appropriate volume for brunch.

This visit was a mix of good and not so good. Made a reservation ahead of time, and showed up a tad early. Hostess was able to seat us right away (good). The way the restaurant is arranged, our table made the ambience quite poor. Facing the large window that faces the main hallway to the VBC, made for an unpleasant dining experience when we were after some quiet and perhaps a small amount of privacy. Our server was perfunctorily polite, but not engaging. My drink order was mixed up and I didn't receive the drink I ordered. When I asked if it could be fixed, server stated that they would have to consult the manager. Not wishing to be difficult, I elected to simply order a new (correct) drink. After deciding upon appetizer and entrees, drinks arrived and then the appetizer. White cheddar pimento spread was good, but not great. Would recommend carrot chips vice carrot sticks for serving. Carrot sticks are not the easiest to combine with this dip. Entrees arrived and immediately noticed a problem. Sides on my plate were incorrect, as were the sides on my wife's plate! Specifically I was given the wrong vegetable, and my wife was given the wrong kind of potatoes. After a few minutes of waiting, I was finally able to notify server of the problem My wife didn't bother asking to replace her side, but I asked for the correct side to be added to my plate. Entrees we did have were well prepared and flavorful. Wife enjoyed the trout and I enjoyed a well-cooked filet. However, after the incorrect drink order and the mixed up sides on our entree plates, we elected not to order a dessert. Overall not a 5 star experience. Would have liked to have better ambience/quiet/privacy, drink order fulfilled incorrectly and wrong sides on entree plate. On the positive side, well prepared and flavorful entrees. However I'd expect more out of a restaurant trying to be more upscale.

Atmosphere was nice and clean, waiter was friendly!  The food was ok... the potatoes had ZERO flavor, the filet was ordered at medium rare, but was rare rare, cold, and undercooked. Odd flavors all around and...The  lemon desert (tonight's special) was like a old cookie with a crunchy lemon candy topping.  I never leave reviews, but for the price,it was mediocre at best, comparable to Applebee's or Chili's. Just needs more flavor.  You have a great location and setup!

MADE A SPECIAL BIRTHDAY PERFECT! New to Huntsville, my daughter chose ROM to celebrate her 19th birthday.  The experience could not have been better.  The service was top notch, the drinks and food excellent, and the people are simply wonderful.  We left feeling full, feeling happy and feeling loved.  What a wonderful place to be.  They know well how to leverage the power of true hospitality.  We will be back—time and again.  And to the FOH staff that took care of us...a sincere thank you for your kindness, for your generosity and for your amazing talent.  Thank you for sharing your gifts with us and for the rich memories you helped make.
Food was worth every penny Outstanding Place
Extremely good food, especially their braised short rib sliders. Great atmosphere and service.
The food and drinks were absolutely wonderful! Service excellent. Can't wait to go back for that Mars mule. Delicious
Great food, and a great bar.

The atmosphere is great, staff was friendly, the food however was subpar mostly. Most everyone enjoyed the appetizers, most everyone did not enjoy the main course. Burger was bland pre portioned Sam’s Club style beef, street tacos  looked like they came out of frozen Jose Ole’ box, fish was good but lacked seasoning. It was all edible but not necessarily enjoyable.
Food was really good for kids and adults - service in the bar area was great.
Excellent experience,  good customer service and friendly staff with a nice atmosphere & of course wonderful food 😀
Service was good.  The food was good.  Drinks are over-priced...I.e. bourbon neat $thirteen for mediocre brand.  Will return for live music on roof 👍🏽
Great food, atmosphere, and service. Good daily drink specials... might have had too many 😬
Very upscale. Moderate pricing.

Excellent Brunch: we made it right when restaurant opened. Enter from Clinton avenue. You can park on north side parking. Spacious place and nice three story view. Food was excellent. Do try cinnamon bun and sweet potatoes fries. Happy to see this eatery in VBC. Too bad that pandemic is taking a toll. They are in news that they are upgrading filters and putting UVA lights soon. They have and outdoor area too.
Very good. And plenty of food. We shared.
Warming environment great good relaxing music
Very good. Interesting flavor combinations. High quality ingredients. We had really good service as well. We'll be going back.
Great food, can only eat apps and drinks upstairs outside.

First time there for me and I loved it! We went straight to the rooftop and grabbed a table with a fire pit! Soon as they got the table lit we were warm and settled in for a great evening of good food, drinks and conversation! The wait staff was exceedingly helpful and continually made their rounds checking in on everybody!
Great patio.  We had the chicken sandwich and several appetizers.  All was very tasty.  Wait staff was great as well.  Thanks for a solid afternoon hangout!

I visited this location last night and I have to say I was impressed with the whole experience of the bar. The food was excellent. The service was excellent. In the future I will visit this location again.
Food inspectors found maggots where food is stored. Beyond gross.
Love the rooftop bar,  definitely a nice place but still awesome
Great food, atmosphere was cool. Very attentive to guest needs. Will be back soon!!!

Here for a convention from Houston.  Life must move faster or I’m impatient.  Tried it for the first time last night and it took forever to get two street tacos and a bud light. Trying right now at lunch. Nearly fifteen minutes before I met a wait person if not more. This under a light load.  The staff apologize without prompting or comment so they know it’s slow. Nice place though.  Food is Sysco like.
Nice vibe. Food and service was unimpressive. Limited vegetarian options. Upstairs lounge area is nice, but only one fire pit was working.
I give this place 5 stars nothing but good vibes from the time you enter until the time you leave. The staff is wonderful food and drinks are great as well. Eric, Ed and Mike made you feel at home

I rarely leave unfavorable reviews but this was one of the worst experiences we've had in Huntsville. I'll start off by saying do not order steak here. They do not know how to cook it. Someone in our party ordered filet medium rare and it came out rare the first two times, completely cold and undercooked. The third time it came out well done. The female manager was extremely rude during this whole ordeal. We left after 2 hours without a properly cooked steak. Every other food item was just mediocre. The cocktails were ok. I'm only giving this review 2 stars because the server was friendly and did a good job. Will not be returning. Do not recommend.
It's different then many places in town. Downstairs, is open because of the windows, but upstairs is great. Two fire pits and plenty of heating stands for those cool evenings. Try it, you will enjoy.
Fantastic place for great meal in good beer, The services always great And the unique menu items are really  unique and delicious.  This is the type of place that deserves a 6th star.
Nice restaurant with good cocktails n nice food
Great drinks, great time, great atmosphere, great people, and most of all great music
Enjoyed  the layout of the establishment.

Good food and drinks based on my one visit.  Downstairs has more food options  and some Gluten Free things that look appetizing but I've not tried those yet so this review is mainly for the upstairs bar area.  Good happy your and menu is attached.  I had the Alabama Street Tacos on Taco Tuesday ($1 each) and they were decent.  Old Fashion was good and the second was even better with a little feedback to the bartender about my personal preferences. Mars Mule was refreshing and not too sweet.  I'd recommend it.  The atmosphere is why I'd come back and recommend you try it.  It was really cool.  Love the rooftop feel and that's hard to find in Huntsville.  4* on food and drinks based on my limited experience 5* on atmosphere and thus my rating

Nice patio and atmosphere for outside hangout and drinks. The food wasn’t anything impressive and the patio serves a limited menu (compared to the restaurant downstairs). Will go back, but probably eat before if you’re really hungry.
Awesome rooftop bar!
Awesome place. Love the rooftop with the fire pits.
Great service
Very cool, modern spot.  The rooftop bar is on point, definitely worth a visit
Best atmosphere and food in Huntsville. The GM Carter is super nice guy! My husband an I really enjoyed ourselves! Would highly recommend.
Very nice place, on the roof, nice view, well decorated, good beers, great environment, friendly, clean, good service, small parking lot beside Mars, they have TV’s and light music on the background.

This place has a Very pleasant  atmosphere.  The restaurant  was well maintained very different for the Huntsville area, it offers outside eating in the front as well as roof top and indoor however; the food I would not recommend.  It could pass for an Applebee’s or something of that magnitude.  I do feel a restaurant of that statue should have a better food selection.  Prices were pretty good for portion.   I had the chicken nacho it was very dry no cheese and  I wasn’t aware it had slaw on top very different.  All around the food was a bit disappointing just not my cup of tea, however; the atmosphere was awesome.  Great waitress and nice staff.  Stop by check it out for yourself if in the area.  If your going for a great meal It wouldn’t be my first selection,  but for an awesome time it’s great in the heart of downtown.

Excellent brunch! The Blueberry French Toast tastes like a delicious cross between bread pudding and a powdered sugar donut without being caked in powdered sugar. You have to taste it for yourself! The filet and eggs and shrimp and grits are also great.  The downstairs patio is large with plenty of space between tables...I definitely feel safe eating there.
Amazing place to go wether it's a night on the town or family nite

For the rooftop bar: misunderstood drink order two times. Pricey for what was being offered. Limited seating for social distancing. People behind bar not wearing masks.  Downstairs restaurant however looked well spaced and following state guidance on safety. Clean and plenty of socially distance seating. Did not eat downstairs as disclaimer.
Great first time visit!! Food & drinks were amazing! so was our server Haley

Great service, presentation, and food! We were able to get patio seating and were served immediately.  Our server was very attentive, he never let us run out of water and made sure our food was perfect.  All staff wore masks and sanitizer stations were made available.

Great roof top location, great service(Good Job Reese) happy hour was good, and I would have given it a 5 except the drinks were ok. I had a mule and it was waaaaay to sweet. We would return for Happy Hour.
Love the rooftop bar
We grabbed apps and drinks on the rooftop tonight. Really enjoyed the selection. The wings are good, the nachos are tasty, but the Jammin' With You drink stole the show.
Great rooftop bat in downtown Huntsville. The bar food was good. Good selection of crest beer.
Went out for our anniversary & what an awesome spot. Good food. The manager Kevin came out and talked to us for a bit. Even gave us a very yummy chocolate chess pie on the house. Highly recommend
Nice drinks and food
Cloudy summer afternoon + fans + good draft beer selection + my bride - - > awesome few hours. Food is good too great. Sit with Cameron.

We went last night for my little sister’s birthday and I couldn’t say enough good things about this experience. We sat rooftop and our server was training, Chris. By the end of the night he was solo and confident with all our ridiculous requests and split our large party check perfectly. Chris was on top of drinks and our food the entire night. His training partner was also amazing, but I’ve forgotten her name. And finally, on her way in, my sister’s shoe literally fell apart. Teresa, who runs Rhythm, hunted down two tubes of super glue and helped her fix it on the steps outside the restaurant. Teresa was also ALWAYS present on the floor and working with and around the staff. Beyond service, the rooftop is AMAZING and is a beautiful escape in the heart of downtown Huntsville.
Bit pricey but the food was good and the drinks were too. The wait staff was quite friendly. Would go again.

Food was good but service was slow. I am not sure if they are understaffed but it took 30 minutes to get my drink. The service seemed to be inexperienced and could not keep our orders on track. I will not be back.
Great service, nice atmosphere, great drinks and food.

First time there -- first impressions:   Nice new venue, particularly the rooftop bar.   Very friendly, eager, responsive bartending staff.   Mediocre food really lets the place down, so I doubt I will be back for quite some time.

My first experience visiting downtown Huntsville and was i pleasantly surprised.  Although they don't have official parking lots the lots adjacent to the facility are accommodating and very affordable.  We had a large group for my nephews graduation and the staff went above and beyond to help us especially our server rusty. Had the Alabama street taco which was very good and a beer. Will definitely return to experience the  rooftop  dining upstairs
Nice, quiet atmosphere, good for small gathering

Great place great atmosphere.  Even on hot summer nights — cool temperatures and a nice breeze.  Food was great - street tacos and short rib sliders are a “10” and I’d recommend it to anyone after work... and whenever corona crisis is over - it will be “the” place to — Rusty was a great server too.  Come downtown and enjoy!

My husband and I had our first date night in a long time tonight and chose Rhythm on Monroe for dinner. We really enjoyed our first visit and look forward to coming back. Our waiters were Rusty and Cameron, and they were fabulous. I highly recommend this local treasure.

My husband & I went last weekend as part of our date night. Because the weather was nice, we sat outside on the ground level, but the interior was beautiful as well. There is a rooftop bar but I’m not sure it was open on the evening we attended. We plan to go back to give that part a shot. Our experience here was perfect. Great food, great drinks, great service. Glad to have it as an addition to the Downtown Huntsville area.
